Glenmark Gets U.S. FDA Tentative Approval for Zolmitriptan Pill

-- B y   A d i   N a r a y a n
-- 
2011-09-26T03:35:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-26/glenmark-gets-u-s-fda-tentative-approval-for-zolmitriptan-pill.html
Glenmark Pharmaceuticals Ltd. (GNP) , an
Indian drugmaker, received tentative approval from the U.S. Food
and Drug Administration for its zolmitriptan pill, the generic
version of  AstraZeneca Plc. (AZN) ’s Zomig anti-migraine medicine,
according to a statement on the regulator’s website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Adi Narayan in Mumbai at 
 anarayan8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
